    "19549372": {
      "title": "Controlled clinical trial of complete open surgical drainage and of prednisolone in treatment of tuberculous pericardial effusion in Transkei",
      "abstract": "Abstract 240 patients with active tuberculous pericardial effusion received a 4-drug daily antituberculosis regimen for 6 months and have been studied for 24 months or longer. Those willing were randomly allocated to open pericardial biopsy and complete drainage of pericardial fluid on admission or percutaneous pericardiocentesis as required. All patients were randomly allocated to prednisolone or matching placebo for the first 11 weeks, on a double-blind basis. Complete open drainage on admission abolished the need for pericardiocentesis (p"
    },
    "13400276": {
      "title": "Adenosine deaminase in the diagnosis of pleural effusions",
      "abstract": "The activity of adenosine deaminase (ADA) was determined in serum and pleural fluid of 90 patients with pleural effusions of various aetiology. Tuberculous pleural effusions, empyemas and rheumatoid pleural effusions demonstrated significantly higher activities of ADA than parapneumonic , nonspecific and malignant pleural effusions and effusions in systemic lupus erythematosus and congestive heart failure. In tuberculosis, empyema and rheumatoid arthritis ADA activity was significantly higher in pleural fluid than in serum, indicating a local synthesis of ADA by cells within the pleural cavity in these diseases."
    }
